Task 1: Prepare Android Emulator Environment
Step 1.1: Verify SDK Installation
Check that Android SDK tools are properly configured:

# Verify environment variables
echo $ANDROID_HOME

# Check ADB version
adb --version

# List available AVDs
emulator -list-avds
Step 1.2: Download System Image
Download a rootable Android system image:

# Update SDK manager
sdkmanager --update

# Download Android 11 x86_64 image (rootable)
sdkmanager "system-images;android-30;google_apis;x86_64"

# Verify installation
sdkmanager --list_installed
Step 1.3: Create Android Virtual Device
Create an AVD for rooting:

# Create AVD
avdmanager create avd \
  --name "RootableEmulator" \
  --package "system-images;android-30;google_apis;x86_64" \
  --device "pixel_4"

# Verify creation
avdmanager list avd
Task 2: Install and Configure Magisk
Step 2.1: Download Magisk
Prepare your working directory and download Magisk:

# Create working directory
mkdir -p ~/android-root-lab
cd ~/android-root-lab

# Download Magisk APK (v26.4)
wget -O magisk.apk "https://github.com/topjohnwu/Magisk/releases/download/v26.4/Magisk-v26.4.apk"

# Verify download
ls -lh magisk.apk
Step 2.2: Launch Emulator with Writable System
Start the emulator with special parameters:

# Start emulator with writable system
emulator -avd RootableEmulator -writable-system -no-snapshot-load &

# Wait for boot (2-3 minutes)
sleep 120

# Verify device is online
adb devices
Step 2.3: Prepare System for Rooting
Configure system partition for modifications:

# Restart ADB as root
adb root

# Remount system as writable
adb remount

# Verify system mount status
adb shell mount | grep system

# Install Magisk APK
adb install magisk.apk
Step 2.4: Extract Boot Image
Extract the boot image for patching:

# Extract boot.img from emulator
adb shell "dd if=/dev/block/by-name/boot of=/data/local/tmp/boot.img"

# Pull boot image to host
adb pull /data/local/tmp/boot.img ./

# Verify extraction
ls -lh boot.img
Step 2.5: Patch and Flash Boot Image
Manual Steps Required:

Push boot image to device storage:
adb push boot.img /sdcard/Download/
Open Magisk app on emulator

Tap "Install" next to Magisk

Select "Select and Patch a File"

Navigate to /sdcard/Download/ and select boot.img

Wait for patching to complete

Pull patched image:

# Find patched image
adb shell ls /sdcard/Download/magisk_patched*

# Pull patched image
adb pull /sdcard/Download/magisk_patched-*.img ./magisk_patched.img
Flash patched boot image:
# Reboot to bootloader
adb reboot bootloader
sleep 10

# Flash patched boot
fastboot flash boot magisk_patched.img

# Reboot system
fastboot reboot
sleep 120
Task 3: Verify Root Access
Step 3.1: Test Root via ADB Shell
Verify root access through command line:

# Connect to device shell
adb shell

# Request root access
su

# Verify root privileges
id
whoami

# Check Magisk version
magisk --version

# Exit shells
exit
exit
Step 3.2: Create Root Verification Script
Create a bash script to automate verification:

cat > verify_root.sh << 'EOF'
#!/bin/bash

echo "=== Root Verification Script ==="

# Check device connection
if adb get-state &>/dev/null; then
    echo "[PASS] Device connected"
else
    echo "[FAIL] Device not connected"
    exit 1
fi

# Check su binary
if adb shell "which su" &>/dev/null; then
    echo "[PASS] su binary found"
else
    echo "[FAIL] su binary not found"
fi

# Test root access
if adb shell "su -c 'id'" 2>/dev/null | grep -q "uid=0"; then
    echo "[PASS] Root access confirmed"
else
    echo "[FAIL] Root access denied"
fi

# Check Magisk
if adb shell "magisk --version" &>/dev/null; then
    echo "[PASS] Magisk installed"
else
    echo "[FAIL] Magisk not found"
fi

echo "=== Verification Complete ==="
EOF

chmod +x verify_root.sh
./verify_root.sh
