Troubleshooting Tips
Emulator won't start:

Check if virtualization is enabled in BIOS
Verify sufficient RAM allocation (minimum 2GB)
Try: emulator -avd RootableEmulator -no-boot-anim -gpu swiftshader_indirect
Root access denied after patching:

Ensure boot image was properly patched in Magisk app
Verify you flashed the correct patched image
Try rebooting device: adb reboot
ADB device not found:

Restart ADB server: adb kill-server && adb start-server
Check emulator is running: adb devices
Verify ANDROID_HOME environment variable is set
Magisk app crashes:

Clear app data: adb shell pm clear com.topjohnwu.magisk
Reinstall Magisk APK
Check logcat for errors: adb logcat | grep Magisk
